content.rendered:
Critical features for natural-looking, safe outcomes.

Natural Anatomical Fit

Proprietary flat back designed to seamlessly contour to the chest wall, smoothing the lateral edge and limiting rippling and wrinkling for remarkable natural results.

High Strength + Softness

Proprietary High Strength Cohesive Gel (HSC/HSC+) with the highest strength to resist fracture, yet maintain a soft, natural feel.2

Stronger Gel-Shell Integration

Greater integration allows the implant’s silicone gel and shell to work as a cohesive unit creating a natural look and feel, designed to minimize wrinkling, resist rupture, and maintain excellent upper pole shape retention over time.2

Unrivaled Safety Profile

Demonstrated strong safety record through prospective 10-year data.3 All implants include the Sientra Platinum20™year warranty.

The Industry’s Most Comprehensive 20-Year Warranty

Covers All Primary and Revision Augmentation and Reconstruction Surgeries

LIFETIME FREE implant replacement for rupture
20 YEAR Up to $5,000 for uncovered fees and costs due to implant rupture and up to $7,500 for uncovered fees and costs due to BIA-ALCL
20 YEAR FREE implant replacement for complications of capsular contracture (Baker Grade III/IV), late forming seroma, double capsule and BIA-ALCL
2 YEAR Up to $2,000 for uncovered fees and costs due to capsular contracture (Baker Grade III/IV), late forming seroma, and double capsule

For qualifying patients with late forming seroma, Sientra will cover the cost of complete testing, based on current best practices, for Breast Implant Associated-Anaplastic Large Cell Lymphoma (BIA-ALCL).

High Strength Cohesive Gel (HSC, HSC+) Offers More

+ More cohesive gel for the highest level of fracture and rupture resistance2
+ More strength with a natural feel2
+ Unmatched upper pole shape retention2
+ Minimum trade-off in softness to achieve greater gel strength

The perfect combination of strength and softness

Sientra implants offer the highest level of gel fracture resistance available without the compromise of an overly firm implant.2

HSC & HSC+ implants show minimum trade-off in softness in order to achieve greater gel strength.2

Over 250 Round Implant Options
6 Projection Levels

low projection | (160 cc – 700 cc)

low plus projection | (80 cc – 440 cc)

moderate projection | (190 cc – 700 cc)

moderate plus projection | (175 cc – 695 cc)

high projection | (190 cc – 700 cc)

Xtra high projection | (275 cc – 510 cc)

Bring your vision to life

  • Our silicone gel breast implants are purposefully designed to deliver exceptional clinical and aesthetic results to support your artistic vision
  • 6 projection levels, 2 gel types, 2 shapes and surfaces
  • With over 200 implant options, our portfolio provides you with the options you need to give patients the natural-looking results they seek

A decade of clinical confidence

Key Complications Primary Augmentation (smooth and textured devices)
Through 10 years, by Patient KM Risk Estimates3

Learn more about a breast implant portfolio truly designed with purpose.

Contact a Representative REFERENCES:
  1. Bellemare F, et al. Sex differences in thoracic dimensions and configuration. Am J Respir Crit Care Med. 2003; 168(3):305-312. doi:10.1164/rccm.200208-876OC
  2. Kinney BM, et al. Silicone gel breast implants: science and testing. Plast Reconstr Surg. 2014; 134(1S):47S-56S.
  3. Calobrace MB, et al. Long-term safety of textured and smooth breast implants. Aesth Surg. 2017; 1-11.(4S):7S-19S.
